================================================================================
1. VS Code Codicons
================================================================================

The SVG icons embedded in `icons/sprite.svg` are copied verbatim from the
Visual Studio Code Codicons project. The sprite uses prototype-style local
ids (e.g. `i-play`, `i-stop`, `i-hd`, `i-floppy`); the upstream codicon
names of the icons reproduced here are:

    add                       (used as the "+" / new icon)
    chevron-down              (tree/section twistie; CSS-rotated when collapsed)
    chip                      (CPU/ROM/chip rows in trees and Images)
    circle-large              ("empty slot" indicator in the Machine tree)
    close                     (toast close button)
    cloud-download            (Save State button, Download log button)
    cloud-upload              (Upload ROM / Upload image actions)
    color-mode                (theme toggle button)
    debug-pause               (Run/Pause toolbar button when running, debug Pause)
    debug-restart             (debug Restart action)
    debug-step-into           (debug Step Into action)
    debug-step-over           (debug Step Over action)
    debug-stop                (debug Stop action, Display Toolbar Stop)
    file                      (file rows in the Filesystem tree)
    folder                    (folder rows in the Filesystem tree)
    history                   (RTC clock node in the Machine tree)
    layout-panel              (panel-bottom layout button, active state)
    layout-panel-off          (panel-bottom layout button, inactive state)
    layout-sidebar-left       (panel-left layout button, active state)
    layout-sidebar-left-off   (panel-left layout button, inactive state)
    layout-sidebar-right      (panel-right layout button, active state)
    layout-sidebar-right-off  (panel-right layout button, inactive state)
    play                      (Run/Pause toolbar button when paused, debug Continue)
    plug                      (port nodes in the Machine tree)
    record                    (CD-ROM rows in the Images section / Machine tree)
    remove                    (Zoom Out toolbar button)
    save                      (Floppy Disk rows; floppy = "save" icon)
    screen-full               (Display Toolbar Full Screen button — enter)
    screen-normal             (Display Toolbar Full Screen button — exit)
    server                    (Hard Disk rows in trees and Images)
    sign-out                  (Display Toolbar Shut Down button)
    trash                     (Clear log button, Delete snapshot button)
    unmute                    (Sound/PWM node in the Machine tree)
    vm                        (Computer / Mac model icons)

Source:
